{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17411376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17411376"},"attributes":{"position":3,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2734"}},"bookmark":{"data":{"type":"bookmarks","id":"1210299"}}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17473768","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17473768"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:14:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:14:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2734"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260986"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T06:24:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:02:58+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":13,"questionsAnswered":0,"marksTotal":0,"marksAttainable":0,"marksAttempted":0,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T06:25:33+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"2734","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2734"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.09,0.18,0.52,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2734"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103514"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2734","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2734"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2734"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85930"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"754"},{"type":"tags","id":"2143"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4972"},{"type":"tags","id":"9690"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3519"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3679"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36589"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43205"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44094"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103514","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103514"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA two-year-old boy presents with his mother to the General Practice clinic with delayed walking and failure to thrive. His family have recently arrived from Kenya. His mother reports that he is cruising, but is yet to walk unaided. On examination, he appears well. He is afebrile with normal observations. He is very small for his age and you note the appearance of bowed legs bilaterally. There is no tenderness over his joints or bones. There are no palpable abdominal masses. An X-ray of the boy\u0027s wrist is ordered (Image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which of the following is NOT a cause of this condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Maternal vitamin D deficiency","Low sunlight exposure as an infant","Excessive strontium intake","Formula feeding as an infant","Low calcium intake"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis child has rickets, which is a disease of growing bone that occurs only in children before fusion of the epiphyses. This results in the classic metaphyseal fraying and cupping of the distal radius and ulna as seen in this x-ray. Due to a general softening of the bones, they can bend easily and cause growth deformities and delayed walking.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA good mnemonic for X-ray findings in rickets is RICKETS\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ER:\u00a0\u003C/strong\u003EReaction of the periosteum\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EI:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Indistinct cortex\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Coarse trabeculation\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EK:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Knees, wrists and ankles mainly\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EE:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Epiphyseal plates widened and irregular\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ET:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Tremendous metaphysis\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ES:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0Spur (metaphyseal)\u200b\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most common cause of rickets is vitamin D deficiency, and this is now mostly a disease of developing countries. Risks factors that can lead to rickets include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBreast fed infants \u003Cstrong\u003Enot exposed to sunlight\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBreast fed infants whose mothers are not exposed to sunlight or are \u003Cstrong\u003Edeficient in vitamin D\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiet low in calcium\u003C/strong\u003E and vitamin D\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExcessive strontium intake\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormula\u003C/strong\u003E contains vitamin D and therefore is protective in preventing rickets.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Rickets has a number of causes, most commonly vitamin D deficiency and presents with classical radiological findings"],"references":["Photo courtesy of Women\u0027s and Children\u0027s Hospital Emergency Department, Adelaide, South Australia (2021)","Kliegman R, et al., editors. Nelson Textbook of Pediatrics. 21st ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Radiopaedia.org. Rickets [Internet]. 2025 [cited 2025 May 23]. Available from: https://radiopaedia.org/articles/rickets?lang=gb"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85930"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2734"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19348"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19348"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c646f875-d022-47a0-b502-5ff782b90e1d.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c646f875-d022-47a0-b502-5ff782b90e1d.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":810,"height":1500}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85930"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-23T11:00:26+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-23T11:01:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2734"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103514"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms"